🌐 Computer Networks
1️⃣ OSI vs TCP/IP Model
Simple Idea

Both are models that explain how networks work in layers.

Mental Model 🧠

Think of two maps of the same city:

OSI → detailed map (7 layers)
TCP/IP → practical map (4 layers)
Comparison
OSI	TCP/IP
7 layers	4 layers
Theoretical	Practical
Detailed	Simplified
Mapping
OSI	TCP/IP
Application	Application
Presentation	Application
Session	Application
Transport	Transport
Network	Internet
Data Link	Network Access
Physical	Network Access
Why It Works

TCP/IP is used in real world because it is simpler and practical.

Memory Trick

OSI = 7 layers (theory)
TCP/IP = 4 layers (real world)

2️⃣ Ports & Sockets
Simple Idea
IP address → identifies device
Port → identifies application
Mental Model (Apartment Building 🏢)
Building address → IP
Room number → Port
Examples
Service	Port
HTTP	80
HTTPS	443
FTP	21
Socket

Combination of:

(IP address + Port)
Why It Works

Multiple apps run on same device → ports separate them.

Memory Trick

Port = App door
Socket = Full address

3️⃣ DHCP (Automatic IP Assignment)
Simple Idea

DHCP automatically assigns IP address to devices.

Mental Model (Hotel Check-in 🏨)

When you enter hotel:

you get room number automatically

Similarly:

device joins network → gets IP automatically
Steps
Discover
Offer
Request
Acknowledge
Why It Works

Without DHCP:

you must assign IP manually → difficult
Memory Trick

DHCP = Automatic IP provider

4️⃣ Email Protocols
Types
SMTP → sending emails
POP3 → receiving (download)
IMAP → receiving (sync)
Mental Model 📧

Sending email:

SMTP → post office sending

Receiving:

POP3 → download and delete from server
IMAP → sync across devices
Why It Works

Different needs:

POP3 → simple
IMAP → modern multi-device
Memory Trick

SMTP = Send
POP3/IMAP = Receive

